title: Greater Sage Grouse
name: Greater Sage Grouse
description: Sage-grouse core areas are habitats associated with 1) Montana's highest densities of sage-grouse (25% quartile), based on male counts and/or 2) sage-grouse lek complexes and associated habitat important to sage-grouse distribution.

properties.About: Annual lek counts help us track sage grouse populations and monitor habitat.
properties.Data: Shown in the map are Montana's sage grouse core areas, regions determined to be critical to the animal's survival in the state.
